# Page Object Model (POM)

## Fixture Chain (read top to bottom)

```
allure.fixture.ts     extends @playwright/test — adds Allure metadata to test
        ↓
amazon.fixture.ts     extends allure.fixture — injects page objects (guest default)
        ↓
auth.fixture.ts       extends amazon.fixture — adds AUTH_STATE_PATH / hasAuthState()
        ↓
spec file             imports test + expect from amazon OR auth fixture only
```

| Spec type | Import from | `test` source | `expect` source |
|-----------|-------------|---------------|-----------------|
| Guest | `fixtures/amazon.fixture.ts` | `allure` → `amazon` chain | same file |
| Authenticated | `fixtures/auth.fixture.ts` | `auth` → `amazon` → `allure` chain | same file (`expect` re-exported from `@playwright/test` in `auth.fixture.ts` — **permitted**) |

**Rules:**
- Never import `test` from `@playwright/test` in Amazon.in specs
- Always import `test` and `expect` from the **same** fixture file
- Auth specs still get Allure metadata because `auth.fixture` extends `amazon.fixture`

## Layer Responsibilities

| Layer | Location | Contains | Must NOT contain |
|-------|----------|----------|------------------|
| Spec | `tests/amazon-in/` | Test flow, assertions, scenario comments | Locators, raw clicks/fills |
| Allure fixture | `fixtures/allure.fixture.ts` | Allure metadata on `test` | Page objects |
| Amazon fixture | `fixtures/amazon.fixture.ts` | Page object injection | Test logic |
| Auth fixture | `fixtures/auth.fixture.ts` | Auth helpers + storage state path | Locators |
| Page Object | `pages/amazon-in/` | Locators, UI actions | `expect()` assertions |
| Config | `config/` | Env vars, test data | UI logic |

## Guest Spec Pattern

```typescript
// spec: specs/amazon-in/search.md
// scenario: SRCH-REG-001

import { test, expect } from '../../../fixtures/amazon.fixture';
import { testData } from '../../../config/test-data';

test.describe('Search', () => {
  test('valid search returns results @regression @positive', async ({
    homePage,
    searchResultsPage,
  }) => {
    await homePage.open();
    await homePage.search(testData.search.valid);
    await searchResultsPage.waitForResults();
    await expect(searchResultsPage.firstResult()).toBeVisible();
  });
});
```

## Authenticated Spec Pattern

```typescript
// spec: specs/amazon-in/professional-test-cases.md
// scenario: TC-012

import { test, expect, AUTH_STATE_PATH, hasAuthState } from '../../../fixtures/auth.fixture';
import { testData } from '../../../config/test-data';

test.describe('Session — Authenticated', () => {
  test.beforeAll(() => {
    test.skip(!hasAuthState(), 'Run qa-pipeline login (stage 2) first');
  });
  test.use({ storageState: AUTH_STATE_PATH });

  test('cart persists after refresh @positive', async ({ homePage, cartPage }) => {
    await homePage.open();
    await cartPage.open();
    await expect(cartPage.cartHeading).toBeVisible();
  });
});
```

## Page Object Pattern

```typescript
export class HomePage extends BasePage {
  readonly searchInput: Locator;

  constructor(page: Page) {
    super(page);
    this.searchInput = page.getByPlaceholder('Search Amazon.in');
  }

  async search(term: string): Promise<void> {
    await this.searchInput.fill(term);
    await this.searchInput.press('Enter');
  }
}
```

## Adding a New Page

1. Create `pages/amazon-in/<feature>.page.ts` extending `BasePage`
2. Export from `pages/index.ts`
3. Register fixture in `fixtures/amazon.fixture.ts`
4. Use fixture in specs — never instantiate page objects manually in specs

## Refactoring Rule

If a locator appears in 2+ specs → move to page object.
If an action sequence repeats → add a method to page object.
